<h2> Welcome!  </h2>
<!--Intro-->
<h4> What is this page? </h4>
<p> I made this page as a personal project to showcase my web development skills. It is about a small TTRPG (table top role playing game) campaign I've been running with two friends for a little over a month now, using a rule system called Brave.</p>

<p> This whole thing stared as an introductory one shot that I had made. I ran the one-shot, everything went smoothly, and we all wanted to play more, so I ended up expanding upon it. This gave me the chance to utilise various ideas I had in the past, that I didn't have the chance to use until now. </p>

<h4> So is this a DnD campaign then?</h4>

<p> Well yes, but actually no! A lot of people tend to confuse roleplaying games in general with Dungeons and Dragons, but DnD is just one of the many rule systems that exist. In this case I am using a system called Brave, that you can find <a href="https://knightattheopera.blogspot.com/p/brave-my-knave-hack.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> here </a> (it's free!'), which is a fork (ie a modified version) of Knave, which you can find <a href="https://questingbeast.itch.io/knave" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> here. </a>
